@Grant

Too late.  The digraph LL was decommissioned as a separate letter in Spanish in 2010.  The Royal Spanish Academy changed the digraphs CH and RR as well at that time in order to make it more compatible with other languages and computer programs.  

The Ñ, however, despite historically being just a way to write a double N, remains a distinct letter in Spanish.
